===Etymology===
From [[w:Jules Antoine Lissajous|Jules Antoine Lissajous]] French mathematician
===Noun===
{{wikipediapar|Lissajous curve}}
'''Lissajous figure'''
#{{mathematics}} a plane [[curve]] traced by a [[point]] which executes two [[perpendicular]] [[independent]] [[harmonic motion]]s, the [[frequencies]] of which are in a simple [[ratio]]
